nt issues to a variety of local businesses and recreational professionals throughout the midwest trucking and transportation are also areas of specialty for david he is experienced in litigating trucking cases in both missouri and illinois and obtained a defense verdict in a wrongful death case involving a truck in pettis county missouri in  david is also no stranger to appellate work he has successfully argued appeals in the courts of appeal for the eastern and southern districts of missouri his first published appeal is hooe v saint francis medical center et al  swd  moctapp for his outstanding work in product liability litigation defense david was selected by his peers as a best lawyer for inclusion in “best lawyers in america” in  and  in  david was named as a rising star by the missouri  kansas super lawyers publication david was also named in  by missouri lawyers weekly as one of missouri’s “up and coming lawyers” background civic activities david is a longstanding regional board member of the antidefamation league of missouri and southern illinois in june  david was reappointed to a second threeyear term on the city of creve coeur’s parks and historic preservation committee professional activities david is admitted to practice law in illinois missouri the united states district court for the eastern district of missouri the united states district court for the western district of missouri the united states district court for the southern district of illinois and the united states court of appeals for the th circuit david is a member of the bar association of metropolitan st louis the st louis county bar association and the defense research institute david is also a member of the missouri organization of defense lawyers in addition david is very involved with internal firm activities he is an active member of the firm’s recruiting committee he is also dedicated to the summer associate program which he supervised from  through  education david earned his juris doctor from saint louis university school of law in  he received his undergraduate degree from the university of illinois in  services product and toxic tort liability sports injuryrisk management industries trucking successes publications coauthor the underride guard controversy and protecting your company in transit august   at  presentations “proactive approaches to risk management” missouri canoe  floaters association’s annual meeting february  “strategies and techniques with health law experts” sandberg phoenix professional development series copresenter “illinois work product and attorneyclient rules and practice recommendations” sandberg phoenix professional development series copresenter “the last  days before trial” sandberg phoenix professional development series biography david hoffman joined sandberg phoenix  von gontard in  and became a shareholder in november  he focuses his practice in the firm’s products liability and general litigation areas david has experience working on a variety of sports injury lawsuits including issues related to supervision faulty equipment and the applicability of waivers prevention of sportsrelated injuries and lawsuits is of keen interest to him as well as such he lectures on risk management issues to a variety of local businesses and recreational professionals trucking and transportation are also areas of specialty for david he is experienced in litigating trucking cases in both missouri and illinois and obtained a defense verdict in a wrongful death case involving a truck in pettis county missouri in  david is also no stranger to appellate work he has successfully argued appeals in the courts of appeal for the eastern and southern districts of missouri his first published appeal is hooe v saint francis medical center et al  swd  moctapp in  david was named as a rising star by the missouri  kansas super lawyers publication david was also named in  by missouri lawyers weekly as one of missouri’s “up and coming lawyers” for